var e=[{front:`What is conditional probability?`,back:`P(X | Y) = P(X, Y) / P(Y): probability of X given we know Y is true.`},{front:`What is Bayes' rule?`,back:`P(X | Y) = P(Y | X) * P(X) / P(Y): relates conditional probabilities.`},{front:`What is a Bayesian network?`,back:`Directed acyclic graph showing conditional dependencies between random variables.`},{front:`What is the Markov assumption?`,back:`Future state depends only on current state, not on entire history.`},{front:`What is a Hidden Markov Model?`,back:`Model with hidden states and observable outputs, used for sequence modeling.`},{front:`What does inference by enumeration do?`,back:`Calculates probability by enumerating all consistent assignments to variables.`}];export{e as default};